Definition: [αἴτιος] from the same as {{g154}}; causative, i.e. (concretely) a causer
[αἴτιον] neuter of {{g159}}; a reason or crime (like {{g156}})
[αἰτίαμα] from a derivative of {{g156}}; a thing charged
[αἰτία] from the same as {{g154}}; a cause (as if asked for), i.e. (logical) reason (motive, matter), (legal) crime (alleged or proved)
[αἴτημα] from {{g154}}; a thing asked or (abstractly) an asking
[αἰτέω] of uncertain derivation; to ask (in genitive case) Compare {{g4441}}.
[αἰσχύνομαι] from αἶσχος (disfigurement, i.e. disgrace); to feel shame (for oneself)
[αἰσχύνη] from {{g153}}; shame or disgrace (abstractly or concretely)
[αἰσχρότης] from {{g150}}; shamefulness, i.e. obscenity
[αἰσχρός] from the same as {{g153}}; shameful, i.e. base (specially, venal)
[ἀκαθάρτης] from {{g169}}; impurity (the state), morally
[ἀκάθαρτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2508}} (meaning cleansed); impure (ceremonially, morally (lewd) or specially, (demonic))
[αἰχμαλωτεύω] from {{g164}}; to capture (like {{g163}})
[αἰχμαλωτίζω] from {{g164}}; to make captive
[αἰφνίδιος] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g5316}} (compare {{g1810}}) (meaning non-apparent); unexpected, i.e. (adverbially) suddenly
[αἰχμαλωσία] from {{g164}}; captivity
[αἰώνιος] from {{g165}}; perpetual (also used of past time, or past and future as well)
[ἀκαθαρσία] from {{g169}}; impurity (the quality), physically or morally
[αἰχμάλωτος] from αἰχμή (a spear) and a derivative of the same as {{g259}}; properly, a prisoner of war, i.e. (genitive case) a captive
[αἰών] from the same as {{g104}}; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity (also past); by implication, the world; specially (Jewish) a Messianic period (present or future) Compare {{g5550}}.
[ἄκαρπος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2590}}; barren (literally or figuratively)
[ἀκάνθινος] from {{g173}}; thorny
[ἀκατακάλυπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of {{g2596}} and {{g2572}}; unveiled
[ἀκατάγνωστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2607}}; unblamable
[ἀκαίρως] adverb from the same as {{g170}}; inopportunely
[ἀκαιρέομαι] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2540}} (meaning unseasonable); to be inopportune (for oneself), i.e. to fail of a proper occasion
[ἄκανθα] probably from the same as {{g188}}; a thorn
[ἄκακος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2556}}; not bad, i.e. (objectively) innocent or (subjectively) unsuspecting
[ἀκατάλυτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2647}}; indissoluble, i.e. (figuratively) permanent
[ἀκατάκριτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2632}}; without (legal) trial
[ἀδυνατέω] from {{g102}}; to be unable, i.e. (passively) impossible
[ἀδύνατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1415}}; unable, i.e. weak (literally or figuratively); passively, impossible
[ᾄδω] a primary verb; to sing
[ἀεί] from an obsolete primary noun (apparently meaning continued duration); "ever," by qualification regularly; by implication, earnestly
[ἀετός] from the same as {{g109}}; an eagle (from its wind-like flight)
[ἄζυμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2219}}; unleavened, i.e. (figuratively) uncorrupted; (in the neutral plural) specially (by implication) the Passover week
[Ἀζώρ] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h5809}}); Azor, an Israelite
[Ἄζωτος] of Hebrew origin ({{h795}}); Azotus (i.e. Ashdod), a place in Palestine
[ἀήρ] from ἄημι (to breathe unconsciously, i.e. respire; by analogy, to blow); "air" (as naturally circumambient) Compare {{g5594}}.
[ἀκμήν] accusative case of a noun ("acme") akin to ἀκή (a point) and meaning the same; adverbially, just now, i.e. still
[ἀκοή] from {{g191}}; hearing (the act, the sense or the thing heard)
[ἀκατάπαυστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2664}}; unrefraining
[ἀκαταστασία] from {{g182}}; instability, i.e. disorder
[ἀκατάστατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2525}}; inconstant
[ἀκατάσχετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2722}}; unrestrainable
[Ἀκελδαμά] of Chaldee origin (meaning field of blood; corresponding to {{h2506}} and {{h1818}}); Akeldama, a place near Jerusalem
[ἀκέραιος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2767}}; unmixed, i.e. (figuratively) innocent
[ἀκλινής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2827}}; not leaning, i.e. (figuratively) firm
[ἀκμάζω] from the same as {{g188}}; to make a point, i.e. (figuratively) mature
[ἄθεσμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5087}} (in the sense of enacting); lawless, i.e. (by implication) criminal
[ἄθεος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2316}}; godless
[ἀθέμιτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of θέμις (statute; from the base of {{g5087}}); illegal; by implication, flagitious
[ἀθανασία] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2288}}; deathlessness
[Ἀθηναῖος] from {{g116}}; an Athenæan or inhabitant of Athenæ
[Ἀθῆναι] plural of Ἀθήνη (the goddess of wisdom, who was reputed to have founded the city); Athenæ, the capitol of Greece
[ἀθέτησις] from {{g114}}; cancellation (literally or figuratively)
[ἀθετέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g5087}}; to set aside, i.e. (by implication) to disesteem, neutralize or violate
[ἄθλησις] from {{g118}}; a struggle (figuratively)
[ἀθλέω] from ἄθλος (a contest in the public lists); to contend in the competitive games
[ἀκρίς] apparently from the same as {{g206}}; a locust (as pointed, or as lighting on the top of vegetation)
[ἀκριβῶς] adverb from the same as {{g196}}; exactly
[ἀκριβόω] from the same as {{g196}}; to be exact, i.e. ascertain
[ἀκρατής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2904}}; powerless, i.e. without self-control
[ἀκρασία] from {{g193}}; want of self-restraint
[ἀκούω] a primary verb; to hear (in various senses)
[ἀκολουθέω] from {{g1}} (as a particle of union) and κέλευθος (a road); properly, to be in the same way with, i.e. to accompany (specially, as a disciple)
[ἀκριβέστερον] neuter of the comparative of the same as {{g196}}; (adverbially) more exactly
[ἀκριβέστατος] superlative of ἀκρίβης (a derivative of the same as {{g206}}); most exact
[ἀκρίβεια] from the same as {{g196}}; exactness
[ἄκρατος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g2767}}; undiluted
[Αἰθίοψ] from αἴθω (to scorch) and ὤψ (the face, from {{g3700}}); an Æthiopian (as a blackamoor)
[αἷμα] of uncertain derivation; blood, literally (of men or animals), figuratively (the juice of grapes) or specially (the atoning blood of Christ); by implication, bloodshed, also kindred
[ἀΐδιος] from {{g104}}; everduring (forward and backward, or forward only)
[αἰδώς] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1492}} (through the idea of downcast eyes); bashfulness, i.e. (towards men), modesty or (towards God) awe
[Αἰγύπτιος] from {{g125}}; an Ægyptian or inhabitant of Ægyptus
[Αἴγυπτος] of uncertain derivation; Ægyptus, the land of the Nile
[αἴγειος] from αἴξ (a goat); belonging to a goat
[αἰγιαλός] from aisso (to rush) and {{g251}} (in the sense of the sea); a beach (on which the waves dash)
[ἀθυμέω] from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2372}}; to be spiritless, i.e. disheartened
[ἄθωος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and probably a derivative of {{g5087}} (meaning a penalty); not guilty
[αἵρεσις] from {{g138}}; properly, a choice, i.e. (specially) a party or (abstractly) disunion
[αἱρέομαι] probably akin to {{g142}}; to take for oneself, i.e. to prefer Some of the forms are borrowed from a cognate ἕλλομαι; which is otherwise obsolete.
[αἱμοῤῥέω] from {{g129}} and {{g4482}}; to flow blood, i.e. have a hæmorrhage
[αἱματεκχυσία] from {{g129}} and a derivative of {{g1632}}; an effusion of blood
[αἴνεσις] from {{g134}}; a praising (the act), i.e. (specially) a thank(-offering)
[Αἰνέας] of uncertain derivation; Ænĕas, an Israelite
[αἴνιγμα] from a derivative of {{g136}} (in its primary sense); an obscure saying ("enigma"), i.e. (abstractly) obscureness
[αἰνέω] from {{g136}}; to praise (God)
[Αἰνών] of Hebrew origin (a derivative of {{h5869}}, place of springs); Ænon, a place in Palestine
[αἶνος] apparently a prime word; properly, a story, but used in the sense of {{g1868}}; praise (of God)
[αἰσχρολογία] from {{g150}} and {{g3056}}; vile conversation
[αἰσχρόν] neuter of {{g150}}; a shameful thing, i.e. indecorum
[αἴσθησις] from {{g143}}; perception, i.e. (figuratively) discernment
[αἰσθητήριον] from a derivative of {{g143}}; properly, an organ of perception, i.e. (figuratively) judgment
[αἰσχροκερδής] from {{g150}} and κέρδος (gain); sordid
[αἰσχροκερδῶς] adverb from {{g146}}; sordidly
[αἱρετίζω] from a derivative of {{g138}}; to make a choice
[αἱρετικός] from the same as {{g140}}; a schismatic

[αἴρω] a primary root; to lift up; by implication, to take up or away; figuratively, to raise (the voice), keep in suspense (the mind), specially, to sail away (i.e. weigh anchor); by Hebraism (compare {{h5375}}) to expiate sin
[αἰσθάνομαι] of uncertain derivation; to apprehend (properly, by the senses)
